00:46.380 --> 00:47.946
<i>on the night of their wedding.</i>

00:51.986 --> 00:54.920
<i>Five miles away,
Martin Hamilton awaits a visit</i>

00:54.955 --> 00:56.855
<i>from his sister, Clara,</i>

00:56.891 --> 00:59.958
<i>with whom he's been estranged
for the past ten years.</i>

01:02.730 --> 01:05.164
<i>She gives him
a black Labrador Retriever.</i>

01:06.967 --> 01:09.735
<i>The same dog Martin lost
eight months prior.</i>

01:12.239 --> 01:13.772
<i>Returned to his master</i>

01:13.808 --> 01:17.142
<i>as if not a single day
had passed.</i>

01:17.178 --> 01:20.012
<i>Along the Gold Coast,
Louis and Christina Selter</i>

01:20.047 --> 01:22.047
<i>lead their 12-year-old son,
Matthew,</i>

01:22.083 --> 01:25.384
<i>on what he believes
is a moonlight stroll.</i>

01:25.419 --> 01:27.319
<i>Too sick to go to Space Camp,</i>

01:27.354 --> 01:30.155
<i>Matthew has spent the past week
holed up in his room</i>

01:30.191 --> 01:32.825
<i>reading
Air And Space Magazine.</i>

01:32.860 --> 01:34.893
<i>He's filled with joy
when he discovers</i>

01:34.929 --> 01:37.963
<i>a gleaming new telescope
aimed directly at the star</i>

01:37.998 --> 01:40.566
<i>that's been named after him.</i>

01:40.601 --> 01:43.502
<i>A small piece of the universe
that belongs to him,</i>

01:43.537 --> 01:47.339
<i>but is shared with everyone
in the universe.</i>

01:47.374 --> 01:50.542
<i>And in a
smart-and-tastefully-done house</i>

01:50.578 --> 01:53.078
<i>in the desirable West Chicago,</i>

01:53.114 --> 01:56.415
<i>Tom Jacobs
checks his phone and smiles,</i>

01:56.450 --> 01:59.918
<i>who is the architect
of these dreams come true.</i>

01:59.954 --> 02:02.754
<i>If he does his job well,
they'll never know.</i>

02:02.790 --> 02:06.325
<i>And for Tom,
